DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: DC link overvoltage
DiagMessage.Description: DC link overvoltage because the brake power of the power supply module is too low.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Parameterization of the brake chopper from the power supply module is wrong.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameterization of the brake chopper from the power supply module.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong selection of the brake resistor from the power supply module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the resistance of the brake resistor. Check the power of the brake resistor.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The brake resistor from the power supply module is defective
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Measure the current resistance of the brake resistor.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Fan speed seems to be zero.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The velocity signal of the cooling fan is zero.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the cooling fan.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Supply low voltage: supply +24V

CauseRemedy.Cause: The 24V Supply Voltage went under 18V.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your power supply.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply status, torque off order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a torque off order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply status inactive

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Power supply status is not alive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please Check if the Power supply status is linked to the Supply Device and the Device is in EtherCAT OP state.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply status, NC handling order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a NC handling order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply status, non-regenerative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a non-regenerative brake order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Power supply status, regenerative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The power supply device is in an error state and sent a regenerative brake order to the connected Axes.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something went wrong in the power supply device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the messages of the power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Supply high voltage: supply +24V

CauseRemedy.Cause: The 24V Supply Voltage went over 40V.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your 24V supply voltage.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Parameter error in Object 0x%x/%x
DiagMessage.Description: The mentioned parameter contains a not accepted value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Something is wrong with the parameters in this object.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please check the parameters of the mentioned object.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync1 Cycle Time (%u ns) is above Maximum (%u ns).
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is above the maximum.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Cycle Time of your NC-Task is above the supported maximum value of this drive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set your Task to a shorter Cycle Time.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync1 Cycle Time (%u ns) is below Minimum (%u ns).
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is below the minimum.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Cycle Time of your NC-Task is below the supported minimum value of this drive.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set your Task to a longer Cycle Time.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync1 Cycle Time (%u ns) is not a multiple of the Sync0 Cycle Time (%u ns).
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is not a multiple of the Sync0 Cycle Time.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Cycle Time of your NC-Task has to be a multiple of the drives Sync0 Cycle Time.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Please set your Task to a valid Cycle Time.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Sync Controller: Configured Sync0 Cycle Time (%u ns) is unequal %u ns.
DiagMessage.Description: The configured Sync1 Cycle Time is not the default Cycle Time.

SubItem.Name: Motor brake type
SubItem.Comment: Activates drive internal automatic brake control.

SubItem.Name: Motor brake usage
SubItem.Comment: Configures the error reaction behavior of the motor brake.

SubItem.Name: Drive on delay time
SubItem.Comment: With the transition of the PDS state machine to "operation enabled" "drive on delay time" is started. The drive follows the command values after the "drive on delay time" has elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to unlock the motor brake before motion is enabled.

SubItem.Name: Drive off delay time
SubItem.Comment: After "operation enabled" of the PDS state machine is removed and the axis is in the standstill window, the locking of the brake is initiated and the drive off delay time is started. The torque/force remains activated in the drive until the configured drive off delay time is elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to lock the motor brake before the torque/force is switched off..

SubItem.Name: Motor brake current monitoring level

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: No Error
DiagMessage.Description: This Message is thrown always, if the Device enters an error-free state.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An Axis entered the error free state.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Short circuit (motor-side)
DiagMessage.Description: The drive hardware detected an over-current on the motor phases. The short circuit detection was triggered.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor cable.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor cable

CauseRemedy.Cause: Short circuit in the motor winding.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the motor winding with an high voltage test or check the winding resistance.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: DC link under-voltage

CauseRemedy.Cause: The Axis got an enable command before DC link was ready.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your power supply device.

DiagMessage.MessageText: [SG], [SL]: Drive overtemperature shut down
DiagMessage.Description: The drive temperature has reached a critical value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The ambient temperature is too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Cool down the ambient temperature

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake power and power loss of axis are too high
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Lower the brake power and power loss of axis

CauseRemedy.Cause: The fan is defective
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the fan

CauseRemedy.Cause: The cooling slots or the measuring sensors are polluted
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Clean the cooling slots and the measuring sensors
